rtificial name, a variant of   Friedland  ."]}]},{"name":"Gertrude","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Germanic female personal name, derived from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>þrūþ</i> ‘strength’. The name is not found in England immediately after the Conquest, but only in the later Middle English period. It may have been introduced by migrants from the Low Countries who came to England in connection with the cloth trade, and was certainly in consistent use in some areas throughout the 16th and 17th centuries, although it was not generally popular until the 19th century, when many medieval names were revived. It has now fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gertrude von Friesland was born from 1010 to 1024, in Friesland, Lower Saxony, Germany. She married Konrad von Haldensleben in 1041. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1056, in Germany."},"et":{"from 1010 to 1024–1056":"1010 kuni 1024–1056","1006–1056":"1006–1056","1025–1116":"1025–1116","1010–1056":"1010–1056","1116":"1116","1006":"1006","Abt 1025":"umbes 1025","1025":"1025","1056":"1056","1010":"1010","1041":"1041","from 1010 to 1024":"1010 kuni 1024","Friesland, Niedersachsen, Germany":"Landkreis Friesland, Niedersachsen, Saksamaa","Schwaben, Bavaria":"Schwaben, Bayern, Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"from 1010 to 1024–1056":"vuodesta 1010 vuoteen 1024–1056","1006–1056":"1006–1056","1025–1116":"1025–1116","1010–1056":"1010–1056","1116":"1116","1006":"1006","Abt 1025":"noin 1025","1025":"1025","1056":"1056","1010":"1010","1041":"1041","from 1010 to 1024":"vuodesta 1010 vuoteen 1024","Friesland, Niedersachsen, Germany":"Landkreis Friesland, Niedersachsen, Saksa","Schwaben, Bavaria":"Schwaben, Bayern, Saksa","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"from 1010 to 1024–1056":"du 1010 au 1024–1056","1006–1056":"1006–1056","1025–1116":"1025–1116","1010–1056":"1010–1056","1116":"1116"